snippet.title: Lina Sardar Khil AMBER ALERT San Antonio UPDATE What We Know.
snippet.description:
Search is on for missing 3-year-old girl in Texas who may be in 'grave, immediate danger'
Lina Sadar Khil was last seen at a playground near her apartment complex on Monday evening. SAN ANTONIO -- The San Antonio Police Department is asking for the public's help in finding 3-year-old Lina Sadar Khil who authorities say may be in "grave, immediate danger."

Lina was last seen on Monday between 4 p.m. and 5 p.m. at a playground in San Antonio, according to police. She was with her mother who left her alone for an unknown amount of time, police said. When Lina's mother returned, the young girl was gone, according to police.A department spokesperson told ABC News there is no indication that Lina is with a family member.

Lina is white, about 4 feet tall and weighs 55 pounds. She has straight, shoulder-length brown hair and brown eyes.

Police said she was last seen wearing a black jacket, red dress and black shoes.

This case is still active and being investigated, according to police.

Authorities are asking anyone who has information on the case to call SAPD Missing Person's Unit at 210-207-7660.

https://abc13.com/amber-alert-for-missing-girl-3-year-old-lina-sardar-khil/11366954/

 Muslim Children Education and Civic Center (MCECC)  https://www.sacrd.org/directory/organization/1644

snippet.description:
Old Hindi Movie Amber (1952) 
Starring : Nargis, Raj Kapoor , Tanuja, Cuckoo, Helen, Tun Tun.
Producer : Seth Jagat Narain, Director: Jayant Desai

Synopsis : Amber stars the hottest screen pair of the time in the lead, Raj Kapoor and Nargis.
Backed by the title role, Nargis portrayed Amber a princess born from a secret marriage between a Prince and a village belle from the hill regions of a supposed kingdom. After the death of her parents under suspicious circumstances, Amber grew up among the village folks unaware of her origin. However once in her youth, the fact is revealed to her and she vows to avenge the death of her parents.
However circumstances and vicious designs of those in power suppresses her efforts. On the way Amber finds solace in the arms of a hero, Raj (Raj Kapoor) who joins her in her efforts along with his sidekick Veenu (Agha).
How the three together finally achieve their goal makes for an adventurous-musical viewing that is both entertaining and nostalgic.

snippet.title: Amber Heard was 'warned Johnny Depp might kill her by accident'
snippet.description: Amber Heard's friend Raquel 'Rocky' Pennington has claimed she warned the actress Johnny Depp might "kill her by accident" when he was drunk or "delusional". ¬†The American actor, 57, is suing News Group Newspapers and its Executive Editor Dan Wootton over a story published in The Sun in 2018 which branded him a "wife beater" - an allegation he strenuously denies. ¬†The case, which entered its third week, continued at London's High Court on Friday and Pennington gave evidence via a video link from Los Angeles, California. ¬†She resided in Depp's penthouse block in LA between 2014 and 2016, and alleged to have been Heard's "best friend" at the time.   ¬†In her lengthy witness statement, Pennington claimed things took a turn for the worst while the couple were in Australia. ¬†She explained that she "voiced" concerns to Heard and said she told her that Depp might "kill her by accident". ¬†She stated: "The first time I became really scared for Amber's life was the Australia incident... ¬†"As soon as she returned from Australia, Amber came straight to my apartment... and told me about the biggest argument they had had to date...   ¬†"I voiced my concerns to Amber that Johnny might accidentally kill her while he was intoxicated or delusional like he was in Australia. ¬†"But Amber continued to think she could help him and that things would get better, and I felt an obligation to stay close for her safety." ¬†Elsewhere in her statement, Pennington echoed Heard's allegations that Depp threw a number of glass bottles at the Aquaman star during the heated row. ¬†Pennington stated: "She [Heard] said that he was throwing glass bottles at her, and there was broken glass all over the ground which cut her feet.  ¬†"She said he backed her up against a bar and she was trying to support herself but her arms were sliding down and getting cut by broken glass. ¬†"Amber told me that at this point Johnny ripped off her nightgown and she was naked on the ground, all wet with alcohol, and bleeding." ¬†She also claimed Heard told Depp had smashed the television and urinated on furniture. ¬†Deff refuted the claims he was violent towards his wife during the row in Australia, and denied he was ever violent towards his former wife and has accused her of abusing him during their 15-month marriage. ¬†The pair married in 2015 after meeting on the set of the Rum Diaries.

Biography:
=======
Amber Heard starred in Paranoia (2013), opposite Harrison Ford, Liam Hemsworth and Gary Oldman. The film was released by "Relativity Media" on August 16, 2013.

She also starred in Robert Rodriguez's Machete Kills (2013), which was released by "Open Road Films" on September 13, 2013 and McG's 3 Days to Kill (2014), opposite Kevin Costner and Hailee Steinfeld, which will be released in 2014.

Additionally, her film All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006), which premiered at the 2006 Toronto Film Festival, was released by The Weinstein Co. in theaters in the fall of 2013.

She was last seen starring in The Rum Diary (2011), opposite Johnny Depp, and John Carpenter's The Ward (2010), which premiered at the 2010 Toronto Film Festival. She also starred in the independent film, And Soon the Darkness (2010), in which she additionally served as a co-producer.

snippet.title: The Reel Review - 3 Days to Kill - starring Kevin Costner and Amber Heard
snippet.description:
Move over Liam Neeson it looks like your arch nemesis is in town! Oh yes giving the Taken star a run for his 'older action man' money is Kevin Costner - back on our screens leading 3 Days to Kill. The big question is though... is it any good? Here's The Reel Deal. 

For more on The Reel Deal subscribe to our Youtube channel https://www.youtube.com/user/thereeldealfilmshow

Follow us on Twitter: https://twitter.com/thereelfilmshow
Like us on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/thereelfilmshow

Celebritain: http://celebritain.com
I Blame Hollywood: http://iblamehollywood.co.uk
Top 10 Films: http://www.top10films.co.uk

ABOUT 3 DAYS TO KILL (12A)

In this heart pounding action-thriller, Kevin Costner is a dangerous international spy, who is determined to give up his high stakes life to finally build a closer relationship with his estranged wife and daughter, whom he's previously kept at arm's length to keep out of danger. But first, he must complete one last mission- even if it means juggling the two toughest assignments yet: hunting down the world's most ruthless terrorist and looking after his teenage daughter for the first time in ten years, while his wife is out of town. Also staring Amber Heard and Hailee Steinfield.

Actor Johnny Depp "threatened to kill" ex-wife Amber Heard "many times", the US actress has claimed.

She described a "three-day hostage situation" during which she claimed Mr Depp was on a "drug and alcohol binge".

Mr Depp, 57, is suing the publisher of the Sun over an article that referred to him as a "wife beater" - but the newspaper maintains it was accurate.

amber heard hot

https://youtu.be/lmTJJRugYrw

Amber Laura Heard (born April 22, 1986) is an American actress. She made her film debut in 2004 in the sports drama Friday Night Lights. After small roles in North Country and Alpha Dog, Heard played her first leading role in All the Boys Love Mandy Lane (2006) and appeared in The CW television show Hidden Palms (2007).

Heard's breakthrough came in 2008 with roles in Never Back Down and Pineapple Express. She received the Breakthrough Award at Young Hollywood Awards. Her appearance in films such as The Informers, The Stepfather, Zombieland, and The Joneses brought her further attention. She next starred in John Carpenter's The Ward, alongside Nicolas Cage in Drive Angry, and alongside Johnny Depp in The Rum Diary, for which she won a Spotlight Award at the Hollywood Film Festival. In 2014 she appeared in 3 Days to Kill, and in 2015 in Magic Mike XXL and The Danish Girl. She played Mera in the 2017 superhero film Justice League, which she reprised in Aquaman.

snippet.title: European Premiere: The Rum Diary | Amber Heard (The Fan Carpet)
snippet.description:
Georgina Wahed hits the red carpet for the European Premiere of the Johnny Depp starring The Rum Diary where she spoke to the gorgeous Amber Heard and director Bruce Robinson.

The Rum Diary. Based on the debut novel by Hunter S. Thompson which initiated his long, distinguished and brilliantly unpredictable career, THE RUM DIARY tells the increasingly unhinged story of itinerant journalist Paul Kemp (Depp). Tiring of the noise and madness of New York and the crushing conventions of late Eisenhower-era America, Kemp travels to the pristine island of Puerto Rica to write for a local newspaper, The San Juan Star, run by downtrodden editor Lotterman (Jenkins).

Adopting the rum-soaked life of the late 50's version of Hemmingway's lost generation, Paul soon becomes increasingly obsessed with Chenault (Heard), the wildly attractive Connecticut-born fianc√©e of Sanderson (Eckhart), a businessman involved in shady property development deals.

THE RUM DIARY is a GK Films, Infinitum Nihil and Film Engine production.

Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†Amber also claimed that Depp was often putting on a facade as he is "very good at manipulating people". ¬†She alleged: "One thing that is important to know about Johnny at the outset is that he has a unique ability to use his charisma to convey a certain impression of reality. ¬†"He is very good at manipulating people. With me, at least early in our relationship, he was able to express contrition after acts of violence. He would blame all his actions on a self-created third party instead of himself, which he often called 'the monster'.  Read More Related Articles  Read More Related Articles  ¬†"He would speak about it as if it was another person or personality and not him doing all these things. I started to do so as well, referring to 'the monster' to describe him during the worst periods of his violent and abusive behaviour, especially the violent incidents that took place while he was abusing drugs and alcohol." ¬†Heard continued "When we were together, it was magic. When Johnny wanted to be affectionate towards you, he was intensely affectionate, warm and charming. I called this 'the warm glow'. When Johnny puts his attention on you, with all his intensity and darkness, it is unlike anything I‚Äôve ever experienced.  ¬†"When I say he was dark, he had a violent and dark way of speaking: the way he talked about our relationship being 'dead or alive' and telling me that death was the only way out of the relationship; the way he would describe what he wanted to do to me if I left him or hurt him (for example, carving my face up so no one else would want me); and in his language towards others who he didn‚Äôt like or was threatened by (detailing how he wanted to have someone tortured or how cheap and easy it would be to have someone knocked off). He could be very intense and dark. It was the polar opposite of 'the warm glow'."  ¬†Heard added: "Johnny attacked me a lot of times, on many different occasions." ¬†The court has already been told that the actress accuses her former spouse of attacking her on at least 14 occasions between 2013 and 2016, after allegedly becoming angry after a drink and drugs binge.  ¬†Depp has denied these allegations. ¬†Amber a

Amber Laura Heard¬†(born April 22, 1986) is an¬†
American film and television actress. After a series of small roles in film and television, Heard had her first starring role in the horror film¬†All the Boys Love Mandy Lane¬†(2006). She first gained mainstream recognition for supporting roles in the action film¬†Never Back Down¬†(2008) and the comedy¬†Pineapple Express(2008). In the following years, she appeared in films such as¬†The Joneses¬†(2009),¬†The Ward¬†(2010),¬†The Rum Diary¬†(2011),¬†Drive Angry¬†(2011),¬†Machete Kills(2013) and¬†Magic Mike XXL¬†(2015). 

In 2017, Heard joined the¬†DC Extended Universe¬†to play¬†Atlantean¬†queen¬†Mera¬†in superhero films¬†Justice League¬†(2017),¬†Aquaman¬†(2018), and¬†Zack Snyder's Justice League¬†(2021). In addition to acting, Heard has been a global spokesperson for the cosmetics giant¬†L'Or√©al Paris¬†since 2018. She also engages in human rights activism. 

Heard was married to actor¬†Johnny Depp¬†from 2015 to 2017. Their divorce drew significant media attention as she alleged that he had been abusive through most of their relationship. He then sued her for¬†defamation¬†in 2019 after Heard wrote an¬†op-eddiscussing being a public victim of domestic violence. He also sued the publishers of¬†The Sun¬†in¬†a related libel suit¬†in England. In 2020, the¬†High Court of Justice¬†of England and Wales ruled that Depp had lost his libel case and that the majority of Heard's allegations had been proven to a civil standard

San Antonio Police Chief William McManus said his department was "sparing no assets, no resource, to try to find" Lina Sardar Khil, who was last seen Monday at 5 p.m. on a playground inside the apartment complex grounds in the 9400 block of Fredericksburg Road on San Antonio's northwest side.

Magic Mike XXL Interview

Segment Producer Shawn Edwards

Segment Editor   Jalen Coleman

The filmmakers also amped up the volume with new characters that introduce unexpected challenges and directions. Amber Heard is the elusive Zoe, a photographer who catches Mike‚Äôs eye; Andie MacDowell is Nancy, an uninhibited Southern Belle who might have something BDR had given up hope of ever finding; Elizabeth Banks is Paris, who must be convinced to allow them a place on the convention bill; and Jada Pinkett Smith is Rome, a woman from Mike‚Äôs past.

As the festivities spill over into a beach party, illuminated mainly by car headlights, Mike has his first of several chance meetings with Amber Heard‚Äôs Zoe. An intriguing young woman with a flair for candid photography, Zoe is someone he‚Äôd like to learn more about, but, for the moment, she gives him only a smile and something to think about. ‚ÄúWhat I like about the way these two interact is that they don‚Äôt follow a traditional trajectory of ‚Äòboy meets girl, boy chases girl,‚Äô‚Äù Heard observes of their keep-‚Äòem-guessing interplay. ‚ÄúIt‚Äôs not about that. We get the impression that they have something to impart to each other which is not possible in their first meeting, though they‚Äôre drawn to each other.‚Äù

snippet.title: Jivin' With Jack| Ep. 08| Loki Episode 2| Trial of Amber Heard|Jon Stewart on Colbert
snippet.description:
Happy Thirsty Thursday! Hope you guys are enjoying the summer cuz we're here to keep you entertained! First we do a another breakdown of Loki with episode 2. We hope you're enjoying it as much as we are!  We go frame by frams (as many as the House of Mouse will let us) and try to pick a part our favorite moments.

Then we have the Trial of Amber Heard! Last week after the title drop for AquaMan 2, fans again clamored that Amber's allegations are reason to drop her from the DCEU! may James Wan will kill her off! But is she worthy of a defense? Well Judge Jack will  hear arguments from Austin as they dissect the timeline  and figure out whether she should be cancelled. Hopefully Judge Jack will be fair. I mean it's not like he made a rant about cancel culture :P

In our third segment Jack and Austin tiptoe around Jon Stewart's epic rant about the contagion that can't be named stemming from a research facility from a city which can't be named from a country that can't be named. This will be a mess, but hey we wanna get monetized. The media is lambasting Stewart's appearance on Colbert. But Is his hypothesis really so far flung? Well if we ruffle any feathers, Jack will send out a deep hearted apology in manadarin while eating dumplings and rocking a fu manchu.

Season 3 trailer for Titans dropped. Good thing Jack  watched some of it and is partially qualified to speak about it...But he'll act like he is 100% qualified. TY and Austin have a new segment that's worth checking out!

Plus any breaking news, we got you covered with bias reporting and scathing remarks. The Talk Don't Stop!
